[thinking] **Clarifying testing conventions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think I need a naming convention for the package that incorporates underscores. Testing outside the library package seems fine. Maybe I should use AssertJ for assertions. I could create a test method to check if the `findAncestorWithClass` properly loads the `JspTag` class. I also need to consider class visibility. Should I maintain one-to-one mapping between report classes and test class files? It's probably a good idea to remove any old placeholder classes if they’re not being used.
