ed to `JspTag.class` being non-concrete. It could be that the static field is affected by previous tests, so consistency is key.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Revising test structure**\\n\\nI’m considering including in the same test a call using `JspTag.class` followed by `SimpleTagSupport.class`. If the coverage is still lacking, that would be puzzling. Perhaps there's an initialization step at build time? I could try adding a test that uses `SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass` with an invalid `Object.class`. It seems to call `class$` but returns null. This approach seems simpler, without needing a parent chain. I think I’ll add the first assertion to keep it straightforward and less setup-intensive.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JcPeM9KjEMvhEKtgqLsMYCA7|fc_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f51429d8048192b6f7bbc91d4888db", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @Test\n    void findAncestorWithClassFindsSimpleTagParent() {\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @Test\n    public void findAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void findAncestorWithClassFindsSimpleTagParentByInterface() {\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport