its behavior, but I want to ensure the first test addresses the expected functionality.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining test strategies**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I could use serialization to reset things—maybe not. Could I subclass in `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext`? However, I can't place the test in the same package, although creating a helper class in the test source under the library package could work. Still, that might not be a solution. I’m wondering about Java instrumentation and modifying metadata, but those ideas feel like dead ends too. What if the dynamic access report isn't covered because there's no `reachability-metadata.json` for JspTag? I might consider adding metadata, but hmm... it seems unnecessary.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test method visibility**\\n\\nI need to think about my first attempt, which was using a package-private method. JUnit 5 does run package-private methods, but could the native test runner be linked to the JUnit Platform? We switched to public in the second attempt, which prompts me to wonder if the initial setup could have been stale, generated prior to that second run. The prompt says two attempts were used, which probably includes both, but I’m not entirely sure if it counts my textual responses rather than actual runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating file status in Git**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether the new file is showing up in git status as an addition. It seems like it might not be. There's a potential issue with the current class importing `JspTag` — maybe this could lead to generating an ldc Class. I wonder if the static field is non-null, but adding a `@BeforeEach` doesn’t seem necessary. I’m weighing my options here carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test structure**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using a subclass in the same package to access the package-private `class$` at compile time. It seems like it wouldn’t be a typical top-level test. I might create a file called `SimpleTagSupportAccess.java` in the `src/test/java/javax/servlet/jsp/tagext/` directory, but I’m curious if that will really work. The rules suggest keeping tests outside of library packages, and I know that top-level test classes need to be public. A helper class might be the way to go.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test runner functionality**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether a custom native test runner only scans class and method names. It seems unlikely, but just to be safe, I'll add a public test method named `testFindAncestor...` with the @Test annotation. The old placeholder class was `Jsp_apiTest`, which might connect to a build that includes only `*Test`. It's possible that dynamic reports were generated before any changes were made, which complicates things. I need to ensure meaningful changes are produced.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test class initialization**\\n\\nI’m considering the issues with static initialization in test classes at build time, mainly due to how JUnit loads them. It seems that native images might initialize these classes at runtime, but I'm not completely sure. I'm thinking we should avoid static initialization and instead add a method annotated with `@BeforeAll`. It needs to assert conditions, but I'm worried about the implications for coverage in dynamic reports. I might need to keep a designated test method too. Let’s make those edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iApqJ8ACjHqL3Ye44s3md6Nq|fc_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f514dd56188192827435207d08605b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @Test\n    public void findAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @BeforeAll\n    public static void exerciseLegacyJspTagClassLookup() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void testFindAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5922, "output": 3204, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30630, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777669295728, "responseId": "resp_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f514b0a75c8192bc330272de225298"}}
