cal top-level test. I might create a file called `SimpleTagSupportAccess.java` in the `src/test/java/javax/servlet/jsp/tagext/` directory, but I’m curious if that will really work. The rules suggest keeping tests outside of library packages, and I know that top-level test classes need to be public. A helper class might be the way to go.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test runner functionality**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether a custom native test runner only scans class and method names. It seems unlikely, but just to be safe, I'll add a public test method named `testFindAncestor...` with the @Test annotation. The old placeholder class was `Jsp_apiTest`, which might connect to a build that includes only `*Test`. It's possible that dynamic reports were generated before any changes were made, which complicates things. I need to ensure meaningful changes are produced.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test class initialization**\\n\\nI’m considering the issues with static initialization in test classes at build time, mainly due to how JUnit loads them. It seems that native images might initialize these classes at runtime, but I'm not completely sure. I'm thinking we should avoid static initialization and instead add a method annotated with `@BeforeAll`. It needs to assert conditions, but I'm worried about the implications for coverage in dynamic reports. I might need to keep a designated test method too. Let’s make those edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iApqJ8ACjHqL3Ye44s3md6Nq|fc_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f514dd56188192827435207d08605b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @Test\n    public void findAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n    @BeforeAll\n    public static void exerciseLegacyJspTagClassLookup() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void testFindAncestorWithClassChecksJspTagTypeBeforeWalkingParents() {\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5922, "output": 3204, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30630, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777669295728, "responseId": "resp_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f514b0a75c8192bc330272de225298"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_iApqJ8ACjHqL3Ye44s3md6Nq|fc_0e4d82b4dd45a7230169f514dd56188192827435207d08605b", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 10 \n 11 import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag;\n 12 import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport;\n 13 \n+14 import org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll;\n 14 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n 15 \n 16 public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\n+18     @BeforeAll\n+19     public static void exerciseLegacyJspTagClassLookup() {\n+20         JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(new SimpleTagSupport(), Object.class);\n+21 \n+22         assertThat(ancestor).isNull();\n+23     }\n+24 \n 17     @Test\n-18     public void findAncestorWith